Module kivakit.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.language.collections.list

Class BaseList<Element>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.language.collections.list.BaseList<Element>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Addable<Element>, Appendable<Element>, Indexable<Element>, Prependable<Element>, Sequence<Element>, Countable, Sized, NewInstance<BaseList<Element>>, CompressibleCollection, AsString, Iterable<Element>, Collection<Element>, List<Element>, RandomAccess
Direct Known Subclasses:
ObjectList
public abstract class BaseList<Element> extends Object implements NewInstance<BaseList<Element>>, List<Element>, Indexable<Element>, Addable<Element>, Appendable<Element>, Prependable<Element>, CompressibleCollection, RandomAccess, AsString
A base class for bounded lists which adds a number of convenient methods as well as support for various KivaKit interfaces, including Indexable, Sequence, Addable, Appendable, Sized and CompressibleCollection. Some of the added convenience methods include:

Bounds

  • maximumSize() - The maximum size of this list
  • checkSizeIncrease(int) - For use by subclasses to check their size
  • onOutOfRoom() - Implemented by subclasses to respond when the list is out of space

Checks

  • endsWith(BaseList) - True if this list ends with the same elements as the given list
  • startsWith(BaseList) - True if this list starts with the same elements as the given list

Conversions

  • asArray(Class) - This list as an array of the given type

String Conversions

  • bulleted() - The elements in this list as a bulleted string, with on element to a line
  • bulleted(int) - An indented bullet list of the elements in this list
  • join() - This list joined by the list separator()
  • separator() - The separator used when joining this list into a string

Functional Methods

  • copy() - A copy of this list
  • without(Matcher) - This list without the matching elements
  • first(int) - A new list with the first n elements in it
  • first(Count) - A new list with the first n elements in it
  • leftOf(int) - The elements in this list to the left on the given index, exclusive
  • rightOf(int) - The elements in this list to the right on the given index, exclusive
  • matching(Matcher) - A copy of this list filtered to matching elements
  • mapped(Function) - A copy of this list with elements mapped to another type
  • sorted(Comparator) - A copy of this list sorted by the given comparator
  • reversed() - This list reversed
  • maybeReversed(boolean) - This list reversed if the given boolean is true
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
